/*
 Text Item Preview: It allows you to display a preview of a text item, such as a word, phrase, or link, within the context of a larger body of text. This is typically used to provide additional information or context when the user selects or interacts with a specific text item.
 Customization: You can customize the appearance of the preview, including its size, background color, and content. This customization helps you ensure that the preview blends seamlessly with your app's design.
 Interaction Events: UITextItemMenuPreview provides support for interaction events, allowing you to respond to user actions like tapping, long-pressing, or swiping on the previewed text item.
 Integration with Text Interactions: It can be integrated with other text interactions, such as custom gestures or context menus, to create a rich and interactive text experience.
 */
